@Node "AF" "Amiga Format Said This About The Game"
        Movie Maker 2 - Almost A Winner Of Amiga Format's Write A Game In
	*****************************************************************
                         AMOS Professional Competition.
		         ******************************


Almost? Why almost?  Well for reasons that are perfectly understandable,
they could not allow the game to win because of it's libellous and possibly
offensive nature.  I understand the reasons for this and thank Dale
Bradford (the reviewer) for still mentioning the game in the magazine.
It was the only 'losing' game that was mentioned.  Thankfully, he still
recognised the game as original and entertaining.  To me, a mention in
Amiga Format is as good as winning the competition itself.

There were "hundreds and hundreds of entries", and for fourteen games to
be singled out and praised surely shows those games are of the highest
quality.

He said "An honourable mention must also go to the authors of Movie Maker 
2, a very entertaining program which, if it wasn't for its libellous (and
prudes may say offensive) nature, would have made it to the short list".
  	               Dale Bradford (Amiga Format - Sep 1995 - Page 26).

(I forgot to include my name and address! - although it was in the docs).
The key word in that quotation is "would", not 'may' or 'possibly could',
showing the game has more or less been included as a winner but for
perfecty understandable reasons has been singled out to protect Amiga
Format from promoting slanderous material.
@EndNode

