@Node "Chapter1A" "Introduction"
		              Introduction
			      ============

Movie Maker 2 is a game based around the movie industry.  Your role 
in the game is as a movie castor and movie producer.  There could be
many aims in the game - the player could choose his own aims (a bit
like Elite 2).  It could be the player wishes to get as many films
to the number 1 slot in the American Cinema charts as possible, or
to make so much money it's obscene.  The player could also want to
break all box office records by consistently creating movies which
smash all records year after year.  But, by far the most popular is 
the oscars night.  The main aim in Movie Maker 2 is the oscars - 
how many oscars can your films win each year - have you got what it 
takes to win all ten?  Or then again, your aim simply might be to
survive without going bankrupt.

Whatever your aims are in the game, I can assure you that if you are
even remotely interested in the movie industry and havn't quite got
a few million lying around to make real movies, this simulation of
the Movie industry will more than satisfy your fantasies.  It has
been in development for over a year and a half now.  I have put a lot
of time and effort into the production of this game and think it's
only fair that if people wish to play this game that has taken me so
long to produce, then they should 'contribute' some money for all the
hard work I put in.

		   See also @{" How To Register  " Link "Chapter4A"}
			    @{" The Author       " Link "Chapter6A"}
			    @{" The Full Version " Link "Chapter4B"}
			    @{" Overview         " Link "Chapter3H"}
@EndNode



@Node "Chapter1B" "System Requirements"
			      System Requirements
			      ===================

The shareware version of Movie Maker 2 requires the following :

		+++    At Least 1 MB Of Chip RAM   +++
		+++      Operating System 2.04+    +++

This version can be made to run from hard disk if you so desire but
you will have to install it yourself manually.  The full version has
an install script which uses Commodore's Installer utility.

		  See also @{" The Full Version " Link "Chapter4B"}
			   @{" Installation     " Link "Chapter1C"}
		           @{" Bugs             " Link "Chapter6B"}
@EndNode



