@Node "Chapter2A" "Disclaimer"
				  Disclaimer
				  ==========

This program is provided "AS IS".  No guarantee is made or implied that
this program or it's contents reach you in an un-altered state or that
the program will run under your system set-up.  You use this program
entirely at your own risk and the author will not be responsible for
any damage caused to yourself or your machine through the use of this
program.  No warranties are made, no liability or responsibility is
assumed.  These files and subsequent documentation are subject to change
without notice.

The entire project was written in AMOS Professional and compiled using
AMOS Professional compiler with the excpetion of the 'Register' program
which was written in 68000 assembly using DevPac 2.0.

The game was created using the following utilities:
Deluxe Paint 3, Deluxe Paint 4, Vidi Amiga 12, GVP's DSS Sound Sampler,
OctaMED V5, Image FX 1.15, ProText V4, TV Text Professional, and various
other PD utilities.  If there are any restrictions on distribution of
data produced using any of the above utilities, my only excuse is I
didn't know about them.

The executable files, data files (visual and audible), and all
documentation are copyrighted to Graeme Blenkinsopp (C) 1995.
There are two versions of the game - the Shareware version and the
full registered version.  Permission is granted to distribute
the shareware version, especially to any PD libraries which may wish
to distribute it, as long as all files remain un-altered and are
distributed altogether.  Permission is granted to archive the files
for uploading to any BBS in the world or network (eg. Internet,
Compuserve, etc.).  The shareware version can also be included in
any compilation (eg CD-ROM collections) as long as the author is
contacted first to ensure you have a legitimate copy.  The same rule
applies to magazines who may wish to include it as a coverdisk - they
must contact the author first for a legitimate copy.

If you have sent for the full version of the game - it may NOT be
distributed.  It is your personalised copy of the full version of
the game - your personal details are hard-coded into the program so
if you do distribute the copy, I know who to bring criminal charges
against.

I read somewhere that if you take a sample out of a copyrighted
song or digitise a single frame from a copyrighted movie you are in
violation of copyright laws and can be prosecuted.  If that is the case
then this game is extremely illegal featuring many digitised frames from
copyrighted movies.  There's no way I could afford to pay for legal
distribution so if the movie producers want to sue me for producing an
extremely small profit making game containing a precious 1/25th of a
second frame from their multi-million pound movies - let them.  Let
them sue me for all my life savings - a whole twenty pounds and make
themselves so much richer.  It's not as if I'm giving the whole bloody
movie away, it's one single frame and it glorifies the actor or actress
and has nothing to do with the movie.  In fact it could persuade people
to actually go and purchase the movie.
@EndNode



@Node "Chapter2B" "Warning"
  	       WARNING - OFFENSIVE MATERIAL CONTAINED WITHIN
	       =============================================

Movie Maker 2 contains some material which some people may find
offensive.  The material is not illegal (i.e. pornography) but
should not be viewed by young children.  The main sources of 'adult'
material are contained within the newspaper headlines, including the
digitised images from The Sun and Daily Sport newspapers.  In this
shareware version, those newspapers are not available but there is
still possibly some material contained within the game which some
people may find offensive. A minimum age of about 14 should be OK.
If anyone has ever played RockStar Ate My Hamster, they should note
that the material in Movie Maker 2 is about at the same level.

@EndNode



