@Node "Chapter3A" "Create Movie"
				  Create Movie
				  ============

You can only create a movie in January.  You can only create one movie
per year.  When you click on this icon, you are given various menus to
create your movie.  The first (and possibly most important) is to select
a main actor or actress and an actor or actress in the supporting role.
A director, writer, special effects company, composer and director of
photography also need to be selected.  Choose carefully depending on the
type of film you have decided to make while taking into account the
past history and experience of the employee.  You will also have to decide
how much money you wish to spend on stuntwork, props, camerawork and
advertising.

For the sake of this game it is assumed that BBFC (British Board Of
Film Classification) certificates are universal and apply to all
charts and movies.  Your movie is filmed during the month of January.
The BBFC then give it a rating (NB: If your movie is too offensive, the
BBFC may decide to ban it).  However, a banned movie will still be
released into the 'underground' cinemas and you will still receive
cash for it (maybe even more).

You then have the option of viewing the opening credits to your movie.
An option which some may think is a waste of time but I actually like
watching opening credits to movies so I decided to put it in as a feature
of the game.

Lastly, a comment from someone who was at the premiere of your movie is
given (the comment will give an indication of how good your movie is).
Your movie will then be released into the American Cinemas.  The
soundtrack of the movie (only in the full version) will also be released.
@EndNode



@Node "Chapter3B" "Publicity"
				  Publicity
				  =========

In the movie industry, the press can have an effect on ticket sales
or video rentals - look at the hype surrounding Jurrasic Park and
Terminator 2.  You could create the most atmospheric film ever made
and it could dramatically fail at the box office if it has no media
coverage whatsoever.  It is important you choose the best advertising
you can afford and issue press releases to newspapers regularly.

However, the press can be unpredictable and enjoy writing about scandals
more than publicity stunts.  Again, however, a good newspaper article in a
well-respected newspaper can enhance a film's publicity beyond what any
TV advertising could.  It's also worth pointing out, a scnadal in a well
respected newspaper will have a greater effect than a scandal written in
a newspaper famed for exaggeration.

You may issue a maximum of three press releases each month.  However, if
you issue no press releases within a quarter, a newspaper will print
a random article about you - it may be good news, it may be a scandal;
the unpredictable nature of the press ensure a random selection.
@EndNode



@Node "Chapter3C" "Charts"
				    Charts
				    ======

In this demo version, there are only four charts for you to view.  Your
film will start off in the American Cinemas immediately after creation.
Six months later, the movie will be released into the British Cinema
and removed from circulation in America.  At the end of the first year,
your movie is usually nomiated for an oscar or oscars.  At the start of
the second year, your movie is released worldwide on Video to rent.  Six
months later, the movie is released on video to purchase.  In the full
version, your movie is then shown on satellite TV.  Various TV stations
bid for the rights to show your movie offering you sums of money for a
number of showings and stating whether they will censor the movie or not.
The final six months of a movie is when it is shown on Network television.

In the full version, the maximum lifespan of a movie is 3 years, in the
shareware version, it expires after 2.
@EndNode



@Node "Chapter3D" "Status"
				     Status
				     ======

In the status menu you have the choice to :

			View Film Stats
			Bank Loan
			View Box Office Records
			Return To Main Menu
			Quit Game

Many are self explanatory.  The View Film Stats option displays how
much money you have remaining, the current year and month and which
movies are currently generating money for you (including which charts
they are in).  Following this screen, a list of all your movies you
have created is displayed along with the cost of the movie, the BBFC's
certificate, the number of oscars it has won and the age of the movie.

			See also @{" Bank " Link "Chapter3G"}
@EndNode




@Node "Chapter3E" "Load/Save"
