@EndNode



@Node "Chapter3F" "Next Month"
				  Next Month
				  ==========

This big red arrowed icon does exactly what it says - it advances the
month.  When you click on this icon, you may be presented with a newsflash.
See @{" Publicity " Link "Chapter3B"} for more information.

Alternatively every quarter you are shown your quarterly accounts
giving information about your income, expenditure and overall profit.
The higher the amount of money you make, the higher your movie is in
the charts.  If you break box office records then your film is doing
extremely well.
@EndNode



@Node "Chapter3G" "The Bank"
				   The Bank
				   ========

The bank is good for only one thing - borrowing money.  You can borrow
5 different loans, each with an increasing interest rate.  You have an
overdraft of Ł25M (for those who don't know what an overdraft is - the
bank will allow you to be in Ł25M worth of debt). However, there is a
condition - if you do get yourself in debt, then you must take out a
loan so your bank account is above zero.  The loan must be paid back
at the end of the year.  The program guides you through any complexities
of the loaning and paying back process.

You may take a loan out at any time and there is a method by which you
can fool the bank and spend far more money on creating a movie without
expiring your overdraft.  Details of which is given in the full version.
@EndNode



@Node "Chapter3H" "Overview"
				   Overview
				   ========

An extremely fast overview of the game for people who hate reading
manuals :

The main process of the game is you create a movie every January (if
you wish - it is not necessary), issue press releases to newspapers
in order to amass public attention, amass loads of cash in order to
break box office records, win as many oscars as possible and become
the greatest movie creator that ever lived.
@EndNode



@Node "Chapter3I" "Oscars Night"
				 Oscars Night
				 ============

You have the option of going to the oscars cermony if you wish.  If
you decide to do so, you are treated to a massive digitised extravaganza
featuring the full oscars cermony including the arrival of the stars to
the nominations and announcements of winners in each category.

However, this is only available in the full version.
@EndNode



