@Node "Chapter5A" "Phreaker"
				    Phreaker
				    ========

A game based off the Spectrum classics 'SatCom' and 'SuperCom', this game
is all about hacking.  You are the world's greatest hacker, last year you
managed to break into The Pentagon and uncover some of the US Military's
greatest secerets.  Only one day, the CIA finally catch you.  However,
the world faces a far more dangerous fate.  The government of Iraq intends
to take over the world.  The have amassed a large arsenal of nuclear
weaponry and intend to use it on the world's major cities if the world
does not surrender.

Nobody knows where their main base of operations is.  The only way is to
hack in through the phone lines.  The CIA havn't got a clue how to do it,
that's why they need you.  They give you a number from an electronics
firm - with your sophisticated hacking equipment you must hack through
a network of machines before reaching Iraq's main base of operations.
Then you have a choice - do you join with them or become a hero?

Over the top plot, I know, but the game is still OK.  The main basis
of play is around obtaining numerical codes and cracking them.  The last
two numbers of most six digit codes are missing, your software tells
you if the numbers are low, medium or high in value.  You must continually
hack at them until you get them correct.  It's not a boring text game
either - each BBS has graphics, some have full-blown soundtracks, some
use synthetic speech and some have digitised speech.

You can obtain this game from Moslty Harmless BBS : (+44 1705 614 824)
The 2 files are called 'PHREAKER1.LZX' and 'PHREAKER2.LZX'.

Or you can obtain the game directly from me : Send :

